I fear that while trying to portray your experience as transparent you neglect to inform the viewer on the full risks of what you're doing to yourself and your body. Not everyone will have the same feminizing effects taking hormone therapy, some men might just get male pattern baldness and more visceral fat, some men might end up losing the cartilage inbetween their bones. Just because you ended up getting fat in "all the right places" for your goals doesn't mean that will happen to all. To pretend that the side effects of your treatment happened as they should and that all hormone replacement and therapy will lead to desired results is a lie at best, and intentionally misleading at worst.

Like so many others in this community, your explanation of your therapy is completely focused on the visual and cosmetic, rather than the intrinsic and internal affects done to you. You're playing a game with your words, and while you may not intend it, these are the consequences.
